Forgive us, America, for sending you only 1300 cases of our best: Dom Ruinart Blanc de Blancs Champagne, 1959

by M. Bertrand Mure, Directeur, Ruinart Pere et Fils, Rheims, France

What we have sent you is all that we make.

You see our Blanc de Blancs is a very special Champagne. It is made only from the white Pinot Chardonnay grape which grows on only one hillside in all of France.

And if in some years the grapes are not good enough, we do not make the champagne at all.

That is why there will be no 1963 and no 1965 Blanc de Blancs to carry the Ruinart name.

We take pride in our name. We are a family business, the oldest champagne firm in France. My great- great- great-great-great-great-great-great-great uncle (on my mother’s side), Nicholas Ruinart, founded our firm in 1729.

From the very beginning, we prospered. We began to serve kings, queens, barons, czars, dukes, earls and the common man. Years ago, we had standing orders from people like Napoleon, Talleyrand, the Empress Marie-Louise and Charles X. And not long ago, we had the honor of delivering a bottle of our champagne to your President, Andrew Jackson.

And now you have it all. 1300 cases of Dom Ruinart Blanc de Blancs Champagne, 1959. The best champagne we make, made in a great vintage year.

We are only sorry we could not send vou more.

A reasonable amount of Dom Ruinart is reaching us but we suspect that it will be depleted well before Christmas day. We therefore respectfully suggest that if you wish to send this unique and remarkable Champagne that you anticipate your holiday needs and order

immediately. SHERRY- LEHMAN N ; INC.
